description.narrative:
- Number of needs assessment conducted among target groups of two districts on business development conducted;
- Number of women provided with start-up business training; 
- Number of women and youth provided with comprehensive training courses on various topics of small and medium business development for existing women-headed businesses from target districts (management, marketing, finance, business planning);
- Number of developed vocational training/modules adapted to the needs of target population, particularly women and youth;
- Number of renovated and equipped local healthcare facilities (hospitals and medical houses), focusing on those providing reproductive and maternal service;
- Number of conducted rapid assessment among  rural women, migrants’ wives and young people  in  to identify opportunities for increasing the local employment;
- Established and strengthened partnership with local public organizations and community groups including women and young people to discuss, plan and implement activities aimed at prevention of negative consequences of unorganized migration;
- Number of rural women, migrants’ wives and young people, including schoolchildren attending 09-11 grades covered with awareness raising campaign covering issues of unorganized migration and its social consequences, as well as advanced diagnostic capabilities of HIV / AIDS and other infectious diseases, sexually transmitted infections;

comment.narrative:
- Women and youth in pilot districts have limited access to start-up business training;
- Provision of support in development of entrepreneur’s skills for women and young people in selected rural areas of the RT is required;
- Access of rural women and unemployed youth to vocational training and professional education needs improvement;
- Access of rural women to quality services in local health facilities is limited;
- Budget of the local authorities and population capabilities is not sufficient to address all priorities of the local economic development;
- Rural entrepreneurship and farms have limited access to the financial resources;
- Rural entrepreneurship and farms have insufficient information for doing business.
